 Buhari today at the State House received the  Governor-Elect of Bayelsa State, David Lyon. Present were the HMS, Petroleum, Timpre Sylva; Chairman Governors Forum and Ekiti Governor; Governors of Kebbi and Jigawa States; and the APC National Chairman. Photo: TWITTER/NIGERIAGOV  The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the governor-elect was accompanied on the visit by National Chairman of the APC, Adams Oshiohmole, Gov. Atiku Bagudu of Kebbi state, Gov. Badaru Abubakar Jigawa as well as Minister of State, Petroleum Resources, Mr Timipre Sylva. NAN reports that Lyon, the All Progressives Congress (APC) governorship candidate in the Nov. 16 election in Bayelsa was declared a winner after polling 352,552 votes. Lyon defeated his closest rival, Duoye Diri of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), who scored 143,172 votes.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .